Revision history for Perl extension Finance::Currency::Convert.

0.01  Tue Nov 28 17:31:29 2000
	- original version; created by h2xs 1.19

1.00  Wed May 30 19:58:27 CEST 2001
	- only the direct conversion rates to and from EUR are stored,
	  but with higher accuracy
	- some debug code removed

1.01  Thu Aug 16 15:49:25 CEST 2001
	- fixed $_ trashing in while(<RATES>) (bkr)

1.02  Sun Sep  9 19:58:52 CEST 2001
	- fixed archive for Windows users

1.03  Mon Oct  8 20:20:18 CEST 2001
	- new function updateRate() to set a single currency rate
	  via Finance::Quote

1.04  Wed Mar 18 00:30:00 CEST 2004
	- fix small errors in the Perldoc

1.05  Wed Jan 2 14:30:00 CEST 2008
	- add fixed Euro conversion rates for CYP, MTL and SIT
	- improved test cases

1.06  Fri Mar 7 14:00:00 CEST 2008
	- fix test case with floating point comparison

1.07  Mon Jan 13 16:00:00 CEST 2009
	- add fixed Euro conversion rate for SKK
	- warn if updateRates() is used, but Finance::Quote is not installed

1.08  Sat Jan 1 10:00:00 CEST 2011
	- add fixed Euro conversion rate for EEK

2.00  Sun Dec 14 14:00:00 CEST 2025
	- fetch currency rates from European Central Bank (ECB)
	- add fixed Euro conversion rates for LTL, LVL, HRK and BGN

2.01  Sun Dec 14 16:00:00 CEST 2025
	- fix reading and writing stored rates

2.02  Sun Dec 14 16:00:00 CEST 2025
	- accept rates file name in constructor
	- fix: keep setRateFile() semanticas to read the file, too
	- fix: don't write unknow rate combinations

2.03  Mon Dec 15 14:00:00 CEST 2025
	- fix: error handling when rate file isn't readable

2.04  Mon Dec 20 12:00:00 CEST 2025
	- add 2 tests
	- improve module meta data

2.05  Mon Dec 20 12:30:00 CEST 2025
	- fix tests when Finance::Quote is not available

2.06  Mon Dec 20 18:30:00 CEST 2025
	- set dummy rates when testing without Finance::Quote

2.07  Mon Dec 20 19:30:00 CEST 2025
	- fix warning when rates file doesn't exist, yet

